text: The information communication licence is based on communication with each other but also the sociological part. There is a lot of opportunities and reasons of why i choose this studies. First it’s because of the news in the tv. I’m very interresting about how journalists work to make an article or do the « jt ». I’m fascinating about this job. First i think people who are doing a carreer in journalistic are vert respectfull because of their knowledges and experiences in real. I mean interviews, reportages, but also travel in the whole world to discover cultures and langages. I choose this studies first because i didn’t have ideas of job but especially for the opportunies that they offer and to, maybe one day, access to this beautiful carreer of journalist. I have notice also that the french journalist Alex Dupont had also make a communication licence in the university of Rennes 2 to begin her carreer. Consenquetly, i think that i want to follow her way! Moreover, my first quality is that i love speaking with people in general and this licence suits me because i learn about how to speak with others but also how to have a relation with others, a face to face speaking…Then, i choose this way for my studies because it’s a large way and i can specialize myself in a large list of masters or schools after my licence. To conclude, during the parcoursup time i have a lot of doubts but now i don’t regret my choices on the contrary i love my choices because for all the reasons i told. If i must quote a person that inspired me it’s obviously Alex Dupont in the TF1 journal.  This webpage performs keylogging of input typed into a textbox. In other words, when focused on the textbox below, the page will record each time you hit a key or select text with your mouse. All of the data is stored locally on your machine in the DOM and is downloadable as a JSON file. More information about the motivation of this project and the format of the produced data are available here.
